' Target-only architecture: ModelManagerInvoker, ToolCallDispatcher, SkillCallDispatcher, RunCheckpoint, and approval suspension are new components.
' Observed behavior: the current loop is synchronous inside one virtual-thread execution and converts every tool call to a local AgentTool execution.
' Java divergence: the target loop returns a suspended run instead of blocking a virtual thread while user approval is pending.
' Design reason: managers own execution policy while Agent Runtime owns message order, run state, persistence, and continuation.
@startuml managed_agent_run_state_machine
